trade.markPriceDesc: The mark price is calculated based on the index price. The price index is composed of prices from major spot market exchanges, weighted by their relative trading volume.
trade.FundingRate1: The funding rate is calculated based on the premium every minute over the past {{hour}} hours. If the funding rate is positive, long position holders pay short position holders. If the funding rate is negative, short position holders pay long position holders. Funding fee = Position value × Funding rate.
trade.detail_usdTips: The quote currency for all system perpetual contracts will be changed to USD. Assets will be calculated in USD, and settlements will use USDT. Changes in the USDT to USD exchange rate will not affect your leverage or liquidation price.
trade.orderbookPctTips: Compare 25 buy and sell orders every minute to provide order reference.
trade.kline_createTpOSl: Create TP/SL Order Pop-up in K Line Area
trade.kline_closePosition: Close Position Pop-up in K Line Area
trade.kline_moveTpOSl: Change TP/SL Trigger Price Pop-up in K Line Area
trade.kline_moveActive: Change Order Price Pop-up in K Line Area
trade.kline_moveConditional: Change Order Trigger Price Pop-up in K Line Area
trade.kline_cancelOrder: Cancel Order Pop-up in K Line Area
trade.marginModeTip1: Switching the margin mode will only apply it to the selected contract.
trade.marginModeTip2: Cross Margin Mode: All cross positions under the same margin asset share the same asset cross margin balance. In the event of liquidation, your assets full margin balance along with any remaining open positions under the asset may be forfeited.
trade.marginModeTip3: Isolated Margin Mode: Manage your risk on individual positions by restricting the amount of margin allocated to each. If the margin ratio of a position reached 100%, the position will be liquidated. Margin can be added or removed to positions using this mode.
trade.leverageTip: Please note that leverage changing will also apply for open positions and open orders.
trade.adjustTipsAddWithMargin_lv: After adjustments, position margin has increased by {{margin}}.
trade.adjustTipsReleaseWithMargin_lv: After adjustments, position margin has decreased by {{margin}}.
trade.triggerPriceTooltip: The Stop price is the activation condition for a conditional order. When the market price/index price reaches the trigger price, the conditional order will be activated. Once activated, the system will start calculating whether to execute the number of orders you set based on the callback amplitude and the highest/lowest price.
trade.midPriceTip: Fill in with the mid price
trade.currencyDetailDisclaim: Disclaimer: The data comes from a third-party platform and is for reference only and does not serve as any form of representation or guarantee.
trade.tposlTip: The default stop-profit and stop-loss orders are not actual stop-profit and stop-loss orders and can only be initiated after the order is completed. After placing an order and executing the transaction, all stop-profit and stop-loss orders will be placed based on your actual transaction quantity by default. If you cancel the pending order, the preset stop-profit and stop-loss orders will become invalid at the same time.
trade.slTips: {{priceType}} at {{triggerPrice}} will trigger a market Stop Loss order. Your expected loss will be {{profit}} {{coin}}. ROI is {{profitRatio}}.
trade.tpTips: {{priceType}} at {{triggerPrice}} will trigger a market Take Profit order. Your expected profit will be {{profit}} {{coin}}. ROI is {{profitRatio}}.
trade.ELPTips: The "ELP" is an estimated liquidation price. The actual liquidation price may differ from this. Please pay attention to the actual liquidation price and margin ratio after opening a position.
trade.costTips: The margin required to execute this order. Reducing a position does not cost margin.
trade.postOnlyTips: The Post-Only order will only be executed as a maker order. If it can be executed immediately as a taker order, it will be automatically canceled.
trade.gtcTips: GTC (Good Till Cancel): Order will continue to work until filled or canceled.
trade.iocTips: IOC (Immediate Or Cancel): Order will execute all or partial immediately and cancel any unfilled portion of the order.
trade.fokTips: FOK (Fill Or Kill): Order must be filled immediately in its entirety or not executed at all.
trade.liqPriceTip: Your estimated liquidation price is affected by leverage and margin. The position will be liquidated when oracle price reaches liquidation price.
trade.marginRatioTip: Margin Ratio = Maintenance Margin / Margin Balance. Your positions will be liquidated once Margin Ratio reaches 100%.
trade.maintenanceMarginTip: The minimum amount of margin balance required to keep your open positions.
trade.marginBalanceTip: Margin Balance = Wallet Balance + Unrealized PNL. Your positions will be liquidated once Margin Balance <= Maintenance Margin.
trade.unrealizedPnlTip: Note: The displayed selected price is for convenience to facilitate profit and loss estimation. It does not impact the margin rate calculation method. Actual P&L are determined by real tradings.
trade.closeAllConfirm: Are you sure you want to close all positions at market price and cancel all orders?
trade.closeAllSuccess: Close all positions  and cancel all orders successfully
trade.estimatedPnLTip: The estimated profit and loss is the estimated profit from closing the position based on the entrusted price, excluding fees. The actual profit generated when closing a position is determined by the actual transaction price and may not be consistent with the expected profit.
trade.filledLost: This order has been canceled as it was rejected on chain. Your assets will not be lost. Please submit an order again.
trade.liquidPriceTip: This price is the liquidation price, which is the price at which the margin loss reaches 0. When the position triggers the liquidation price, the forced liquidation order will be liquidated by the liquidation engine at the liquidation price.
trade.liquidPriceAdditionalTip: Note: The liquidation order execution occurs through over-the-counter matching; as a result, the takeover price of the liquidation order will not be displayed on the K-line.
trade.reason_0: Errors were detected with your order. To ensure the safety of your assets, this order has been automatically canceled.
trade.reason_2: User has initiated cancellation of the order.
trade.reason_3: This order has expired and will be automatically canceled.
trade.reason_4: This order has triggered Post-Only, FOK, IOC or GTT conditions and will be automatically canceled.
trade.reason_5: Order does not fulfil the conditions of a Reduce-Only order and will be automatically canceled.
trade.reason_6: Due to margin insufficiency, the order has been automatically canceled.
trade.reason_7: Due to forced liquidation, the order will be automatically canceled.
trade.reason_8: Due to errors in your order, the order has been automatically canceled to ensure the safety of your assets.
trade.reduceOnlyTip: The Reduce-Only order will only reduce your position size. Any order that might increase your position size will be canceled or adjusted.
trade.timeInForceTip: Time In Force includes: Post Only, Good Till Time, Immediate Or Cancel, Fill Or Kill.
trade.longFormulaClosedPnLTip: Realized P&L = Close Value - Open Value - Trading Fees + Funding Fees
trade.shortFormulaClosedPnLTip: Realized P&L = Open Value - Close Value - Trading Fees + Funding Fees
trade.closeFeeTip: Close Fee = Fees incurred to open a position + Fees incurred to close a position + Liquidation fees
trade.slippageTips: Average execution price compared to mid price based on current order book
trade.feesTips: Taker orders pay a {{taker}} fee. Maker orders pay a {{maker}} fee.
trade.tpPriceLessTips: The Take Profit price can't be less than the {{priceType}}.
trade.tpPriceMoreTips: The Take Profit price can't be more than the {{priceType}}.
trade.slPriceLessTips: The Stop Loss price can't be less than the {{priceType}}.
trade.slPriceMoreTips: The Stop Loss price can't be more than the {{priceType}}.
trade.oraclePriceDesc: The oracle price draws data from an external independent node service provider, which is used to calculate your liquidation price and position margin.
trade.cancelOrderToChangeLeverage: Please cancel all open orders and  position TP/SL then try again.
trade.orderPriceMoreThanOraclePriceRatio: Order price is higher than stop price multiplier cap. {{price}}
trade.orderPriceLessThanOraclePriceRatio: Order price is lower than stop price multiplier cap. {{price}}

trade.shortTPPriceError: TP price must be less than entry price
trade.longSLPriceError: SL price must be less than entry price
trade.shortSLPriceError: SL price must be greater than entry price
trade.openPositionTpOSlTips: TP/SL must be on the same side as the position
trade.closePositionToChangeMarginMode: Please close all positions and try again.
trade.leverageChangeTip: The leverage will be increased once the margin is reduced
